blocks.name: wbr
blocks.content: Extend wff notation to include the general binary relation predicate. Note that the syntax is simply three class symbols in a row. Since binary relations are the only possible wff expressions consisting of three class expressions in a row, the syntax is unambiguous. (For an example of how syntax could become ambiguous if we are not careful, see the comment in ~ cneg .)
blocks.origin: prop wff wbr(class c0, class c1, class c2) { c0[c1]c2 }

df-br
blocks.content: Define a general binary relation. Note that the syntax is simply three class symbols in a row. Definition 6.18 of [TakeutiZaring] p. 29 generalized to arbitrary classes. Class ` R ` often denotes a relation such as " ` < ` " that compares two classes ` A ` and ` B ` , which might be numbers such as ` 1 ` and ` 2 ` (see ~ df-ltxr for the specific definition of ` < ` ). As a wff, relations are true or false. For example, ` ( R = { <. 2 , 6 >. , <. 3 , 9 >. } -> 3 R 9 ) ` ( ~ ex-br ). Often class ` R ` meets the ` Rel ` criteria to be defined in ~ df-rel , and in particular ` R ` may be a function (see ~ df-fun ). This definition of relations is well-defined, although not very meaningful, when classes ` A ` and/or ` B ` are proper classes (i.e. are not sets). On the other hand, we often find uses for this definition when ` R ` is a proper class (see for example ~ iprc ). (Contributed by NM, 31-Dec-1993.)

thm brab1(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1) {
  |- wb(wbr(cv(s0), c0, c1), wcel(cv(s0), cab(s1, wbr(cv(s1), c0, c1))))
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
} = {
  bitr3i(wbr(cv(s0), c0, c1), wcel(cv(s0), cab(s1, wbr(cv(s1), c0, c1))), wsbc(s1, cv(s0), wbr(cv(s1), c0, c1)))
  elv(s0, wb(wsbc(s1, cv(s0), wbr(cv(s1), c0, c1)), wbr(cv(s0), c0, c1)))
  sbcie2g(s1, hs0, cv(s0), universe, wbr(cv(s1), c0, c1), wbr(cv(s0), c0, c1), wbr(cv(hs0), c0, c1))
  breq1(cv(s1), cv(hs0), c0, c1)
  breq1(cv(hs0), cv(s0), c0, c1)
  df-sbc(s1, cv(s0), wbr(cv(s1), c0, c1))
  diff.hs0.c(cv(s0))
  diff.wbr.s(s1, cv(hs0), c0, c1)
  diff.cv.s(s1, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s1, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s1)
  diff.hs0.w(wbr(cv(s1), c0, c1))
  diff.hs0.w(wbr(cv(s0), c0, c1))
}

thm brab1(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1) {
  ⊢ (s0[c0]c1 ↔ s0 ∈ { s1 | s1[c0]c1 })
  ⊣ d(s1, c0)
  ⊣ d(s1, c1)
} = {
  bitr3i(s0[c0]c1, s0 ∈ { s1 | s1[c0]c1 }, [s0 / s1]s1[c0]c1)
  elv(s0, ([s0 / s1]s1[c0]c1 ↔ s0[c0]c1))
  sbcie2g(s1, hs0, s0, universe, s1[c0]c1, s0[c0]c1, hs0[c0]c1)
  breq1(s1, hs0, c0, c1)
  breq1(hs0, s0, c0, c1)
  df-sbc(s1, s0, s1[c0]c1)
  diff.hs0.c(s0)
  diff.wbr.s(s1, hs0, c0, c1)
  diff.cv.s(s1, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s1, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s1)
  diff.hs0.w(s1[c0]c1)
  diff.hs0.w(s0[c0]c1)
}

} = {
  pm5.21nii(wsbc(s0, c0, wbr(c1, c2, c3)), wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3)), wcel(c0, universe))
  sbcex(s0, c0, wbr(c1, c2, c3))
  con4i(wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3)), wcel(c0, universe))
  mtbiri(wn(wcel(c0, universe)), wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3)), wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), emptycls, csb(s0, c0, c3)))
  br0(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c3))
  breqd(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3), emptycls, wn(wcel(c0, universe)))
  csbprc(s0, c0, c2)
  vtoclbg(hs0, c0, universe, wsbc(s0, c0, wbr(c1, c2, c3)), wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3)), wsb(hs0, s0, wbr(c1, c2, c3)), wbr(csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c3)))
  dfsbcq2(hs0, s0, c0, wbr(c1, c2, c3))
  breq123d(csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c3), csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3), wceq(cv(hs0), c0))
  csbeq1(s0, cv(hs0), c0, c1)
  csbeq1(s0, cv(hs0), c0, c2)
  csbeq1(s0, cv(hs0), c0, c3)
  sbie(hs0, s0, wbr(c1, c2, c3), wbr(csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c3)))
  nfbr(s0, csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c3))
  nfcsb1v(s0, cv(hs0), c1)
  nfcsb1v(s0, cv(hs0), c2)
  nfcsb1v(s0, cv(hs0), c3)
  breq123d(c1, c2, c3, csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c3), wceq(cv(s0), cv(hs0)))
  csbeq1a(s0, cv(hs0), c1)
  csbeq1a(s0, cv(hs0), c2)
  csbeq1a(s0, cv(hs0), c3)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.w(wsbc(s0, c0, wbr(c1, c2, c3)))
  diff.hs0.w(wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3)))
  diff.cv.s(s0, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s0, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
}

thm sbcbr123(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3) {
  ⊢ ([c0 / s0]c1[c2]c3 ↔[c0 / s0]c1[[c0 / s0]c2][c0 / s0]c3)

  breqd([c0 / s0]c1, [c0 / s0]c2, [c0 / s0]c3, emptycls, ¬ c0 ∈ 𝕌)
  csbprc(s0, c0, c2)
  vtoclbg(hs0, c0, universe, [c0 / s0]c1[c2]c3, [c0 / s0]c1[[c0 / s0]c2][c0 / s0]c3, [hs0 / s0]c1[c2]c3, [hs0 / s0]c1[[hs0 / s0]c2][hs0 / s0]c3)
  dfsbcq2(hs0, s0, c0, c1[c2]c3)
  breq123d([hs0 / s0]c1, [hs0 / s0]c2, [hs0 / s0]c3, [c0 / s0]c1, [c0 / s0]c2, [c0 / s0]c3, hs0 = c0)
  csbeq1(s0, hs0, c0, c1)
  csbeq1(s0, hs0, c0, c2)
  csbeq1(s0, hs0, c0, c3)
  sbie(hs0, s0, c1[c2]c3, [hs0 / s0]c1[[hs0 / s0]c2][hs0 / s0]c3)
  nfbr(s0, [hs0 / s0]c1, [hs0 / s0]c2, [hs0 / s0]c3)
  nfcsb1v(s0, hs0, c1)
  nfcsb1v(s0, hs0, c2)
  nfcsb1v(s0, hs0, c3)
  breq123d(c1, c2, c3, [hs0 / s0]c1, [hs0 / s0]c2, [hs0 / s0]c3, s0 = hs0)
  csbeq1a(s0, hs0, c1)

  diff.hs0.c(c0)

thm sbcbr(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3) {
  |- wb(wsbc(s0, c0, wbr(c1, c2, c3)), wbr(c1, csb(s0, c0, c2), c3))
  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c3)

  bitri(wsbc(s0, c0, wbr(c1, c2, c3)), wbr(c1, csb(s0, c0, c2), c3), wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3)))
  sbcbr123(s0, c0, c1, c2, c3)
  pm2.61i(wb(wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3)), wbr(c1, csb(s0, c0, c2), c3)), wcel(c0, universe))
  breq12d(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3), c1, c3, wcel(c0, universe))
  csbconstg(s0, c0, universe, c1)
  csbconstg(s0, c0, universe, c3)
  2falsed(wn(wcel(c0, universe)), wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3)), wbr(c1, csb(s0, c0, c2), c3))
  mtbiri(wn(wcel(c0, universe)), wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3)), wbr(csb(s0, c0, c1), emptycls, csb(s0, c0, c3)))
  br0(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c3))
  breqd(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), csb(s0, c0, c3), emptycls, wn(wcel(c0, universe)))
  mtbiri(wn(wcel(c0, universe)), wbr(c1, csb(s0, c0, c2), c3), wbr(c1, emptycls, c3))

thm brralrspcev(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4) {
  |- wi(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wral(s0, c2, wbr(c3, c4, c0))), wrex(s1, c1, wral(s0, c2, wbr(c3, c4, cv(s1)))))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
  -| diffsc(s1, c2)
  -| diffsc(s1, c3)
  -| diffsc(s1, c4)
} = {
  rspcev(s1, c0, c1, wral(s0, c2, wbr(c3, c4, c0)), wral(s0, c2, wbr(c3, c4, cv(s1))))
  ralbidv(s0, c2, wceq(cv(s1), c0), wbr(c3, c4, cv(s1)), wbr(c3, c4, c0))
  breq2(cv(s1), c0, c3, c4)
  diff.wral.s(s1, s0, c2, wbr(c3, c4, c0))
  diffss.ex(s1, s0)
  diff.wbr.s(s1, c3, c4, c0)
  diff.wceq.s(s0, cv(s1), c0)
  diff.cv.s(s0, s1)
}

  ⊢ ((c0 ∈ c1 ∧ ∀(s0 ∈ c2, c3[c4]c0))→ ∃(s1 ∈ c1, ∀(s0 ∈ c2, c3[c4]s1)))
  ⊣ d(s0, s1)

  ⊣ d(s1, c0)

  ⊣ d(s1, c4)
} = {
  rspcev(s1, c0, c1, ∀(s0 ∈ c2, c3[c4]c0), ∀(s0 ∈ c2, c3[c4]s1))
  ralbidv(s0, c2, s1 = c0, c3[c4]s1, c3[c4]c0)
  breq2(s1, c0, c3, c4)
  diff.wral.s(s1, s0, c2, c3[c4]c0)
  diffss.ex(s1, s0)
  diff.wbr.s(s1, c3, c4, c0)
  diff.wceq.s(s0, s1, c0)
  diff.cv.s(s0, s1)
}
